rotcheck
------------------------------------------
A simple shell script to recursively generate, update and verify checksums for
files you care about. It's useful for detecting bit rot.

Runtime requirements:
  bash-4.4.12-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygport-0.34.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/jamielinux/rotcheck

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/jamielinux/rotcheck/archive/v1.1.2.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack rotcheck-1.1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./rotcheck-1.1.2-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/rotcheck-1.1.2-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/rotcheck-1.1.2-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(rotcheck)
  /usr/bin/rotcheck
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/rotcheck.README
  /usr/share/doc/rotcheck/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/rotcheck/README.md

